	)
	(text "Output modes:\nAll power transistors should be the same.\nChoose (Q1, Q5, Q9, Q13), (Q2, Q6, Q10, Q14) or (Q3, Q7, Q11, Q15)\nIf the power transistor is saturated for the projected current \nwhen V_gs = 3.3V use the inversion. To use the inversion:\n* open JP1, JP5, JP6, JP8;\n* insert R1, Q4, R6, Q8, R11, Q12, R13, Q16.\nFor non-inverting mode, close the jumpers \nand do not insert elements listed above.\nFor three-channel output, just skip any output section.\n\nPower modes:\nPossible configurations:\n* Pulse regulator and no linear regulator - close JP2, skip U1.\n* Pulse regulator and linear regulator - close JP3, skip R5 and R6.\n* No pulse regulator and linear regulator - close JP4, skip \n  all parts of \"Pulse regulator\".\n\nResistors:\nAll resistors without given values should be the same \nand have a value between 1kOhm and 4.7kOhm"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 111.506 168.402 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.2 1.2)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "b504ec5a-ab76-4d2d-bf3a-cb0a5fed56e8")
	)
	(text "For potentiometers 10k:\n* 1x1k\n* 2x2.2k\n* 3x3.3k\n* 3x4.7k"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 159.512 36.83 0)
		(effects
